climbs.name: Snacks and Sunshine
climbs.fa: Alex Hill, Alex Wodarczk, Jim Borton, March 24, 2019

content.description: This is a project.  The rating is a guess.
content.protection: TBD.  Looks like small cams and tricams.  Maybe a nut or two.
content.location: The obvious overhanging crack and vicinity on the Underlook.

content.description: A small subsidiary crag below and slightly downstream from the Gunpowder Overlook, very close to the Gunpowder South trail. 25 feet high. Top roping. Maybe one leadable route—an overhanging finger crack.  Bouldering, too. Relatively flat landing area with a bed of leaves. Rock is very sharp.  The Underlook faces southwest and gets nice winter sun.
